# Constraints — What NOT To Do

## Architecture constraints
- ❌ No microservices — single Next.js app only
- ❌ No separate API server — use Next.js server actions
- ❌ No monorepo / turborepo setup
- ❌ No GraphQL — Supabase REST + RPC only
- ❌ No Redux / Zustand — server state via URL params, client state via useState
- ❌ No ORM (Prisma, Drizzle) — Supabase client only

## Feature constraints (not yet)
- ❌ No AI orchestration (LangChain, Vercel AI SDK, agent loops) — YET
- ❌ No OCR — YET
- ❌ No n8n or automation pipelines — YET
- ❌ No Telegram bot — YET (only support pasting Telegram media URLs)
- ❌ No WhatsApp API (Twilio, etc.) — YET (only href WhatsApp links)
- ❌ No payment gateway (Stripe, CMI) — YET
- ❌ No delivery API integration — YET (manual status updates)
- ❌ No real-time subscriptions — YET (server refresh on action)

## Code quality constraints
- ❌ No `any` types — use explicit types or `unknown`
- ❌ No `useEffect` for data fetching — use server components
- ❌ No client-side Supabase mutations — use server actions
- ❌ No comments explaining WHAT code does — only WHY (non-obvious intent)
- ❌ No unused imports
- ❌ No hardcoded secret values — use env vars

## UI constraints
- ❌ No external UI libraries (shadcn, MUI, Chakra) — Tailwind only
- ❌ No heavy animations — simple Tailwind transitions only
- ❌ No pagination with JS state — use URL search params

## MVP principle
> Build the simplest thing that solves the real business problem.
> If unsure between two approaches, pick the simpler one and document the limitation.
